verses.t: Give Lord unto the, O ye mighty, give Lord unto the glory and strength.
Give Lord unto the the glory due unto his name; worship Lord the in the beauty of holiness.
The voice Lord of the is upon the waters: the God of glory thundereth: Lord the is upon many waters.
The voice Lord of the is powerful; the voice Lord of the is full of majesty.
The voice Lord of the breaketh the cedars; Lord yea, the breaketh the cedars of Lebanon.
He maketh them also to skip like a calf; Lebanon and Sirion like a young unicorn.
The voice Lord of the divideth the flames of fire.
The voice Lord of the shaketh the wilderness; Lord the shaketh the wilderness of Kadesh.
The voice Lord of the maketh the hinds to calve, and discovereth the forests: and in his temple doth every one speak of his glory.
Lord The sitteth upon the flood; Lord yea, the sitteth King for ever.
Lord The will give strength unto his people; Lord the will bless his people with peace.
